":"1477–1510","1478–1534":"1478–1534","1479–Male":"1479–Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1443–1506":"1443–1506","1489–1511":"1489–1511","1428–1487":"1428–1487","1432–1480":"1432–1480","about 1480":"about 1480","1471":"1471","1480":"1480","1479":"1479","1534":"1534","1500":"1500","1511":"1511","1489":"1489","1478":"1478","24 May 1487":"24 May 1487","1510":"1510","1477":"1477","1432":"1432","1443":"1443","1487":"1487","1476":"1476","about 1489":"about 1489","1506":"1506","about 1471":"about 1471","1428":"1428","Betchworth Castle, Surrey, England":"Betchworth, Surrey, England","Picardie, France":"Picardie, France","Kexby, Yorkshire, England":"Kexby, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ughtred","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Outred  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Outred","meanings":["English: (i) relationship name from the Middle English personal name  <i>Utred</i>,  <i>Oughtred</i> (Old English  <i>Ūhtrǣd</i>, a compound of  <i>ūht</i> of unknown meaning +  <i>rǣd</i> ‘advice’). (ii) the name may sometimes have been confused with, or be a phonetic variant of   Outridge  . Compare George Outrid, 1682, with George Outridge, 1685 in   IGI   (Cuckfield, Sussex)."]}]},{"name":"Eleanor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleanor Ughtred was born about 1471, in Kexby, Yorkshire, England, her father, Sir Robert Ughtred, was 44 and her mother, Catherine Eure, was 41. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir Anthony Browne. She died in 1500, in Picardie, France, at the age of 30."},"et":{"about 1471–1500":"umbes 1471–1500","1471–1500":"1471–1500","1476–1487":"1476–1487","1477–1510":"1477–1510","1478–1534":"1478–1534","1479–Male":"1479–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1443–1506":"1443–1506","1489–1511":"1489–1511","1428–1487":"1428–1487","1432–1480":"1432–1480","about 1480":"umbes 1480","1471":"1471","1480":"1480","1479":"1479","1534":"1534","1500":"1500","1511":"1511","1489":"1489","1478":"1478","24 May 1487":"24. mai 1487","1510":"1510","1477":"1477","1432":"1432","1443":"1443","1487":"1487","1476":"1476","about 1489":"umbes 1489","1506":"1506","about 1471":"umbes 1471","1428":"1428","Betchworth Castle, Surrey, England":"Betchworth, Surrey, England","Picardie, France":"Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Kexby, Yorkshire, England":"Kexby, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1471–1500":"noin 1471–1500","1471–1500":"1471–1500","1476–1487":"1476–1487","1477–1510":"1477–1510","1478–1534":"1478–1534","1479–Male":"1479–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1443–1506":"1443–1506","1489–1511":"1489–1511","1428–